[{"id":"VH950785","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a triangle in the coordinate plane with origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled x, in meters, and the vertical axis is labeled y, in meters. The left vertex of the triangle is located at the point negative x comma 0, and a point with a charge of positive q is located at the vertex. The right vertex of the triangle is located at the point x comma 0, and a point with a charge of negative q is located at the vertex. The top vertex is located at the point 0 comma y, and the left and right sides of the triangle both have a length of r.\" height=\"179\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH950785.g01.png\" width=\"310\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A point charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative q\"><math alttext=\"negative q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the point x comma 0\"><math alttext=\"the point x comma 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and a point charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q \"><math alttext=\"positive q \" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the point negative x comma 0\"><math alttext=\"the point negative x comma 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown. What are the magnitude and direction of the electric field created by these point charges at the point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"th